Cell["\<\
Description: 
The circle of radius 1, centered around the origin is plotted in blue. The \
line passing though the North pole is plotted in red. As the slider is moved, \
the intersection of the red line and the circle (denoted as \
\[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]O\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote]) and the intersection of the \
red line and the x-axis (denoted as \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]X\
\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote]) moves. Using the stereographic projection map, the \
points denoted as \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]O\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] on the \
circle are mapped to \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]X\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] on \
x-axis.\
\>", "Text",
